node.text: Porsche is in the minds of many the ultimate sports car brand. Its cars – especially its legendary 911 – blend high performance with quality construction and even a solid reputation for dependability. But the brand that made its name with small nimble two-door sports cars ruffled feathers in the automotive world when it tried its hand at a four-door sport utility vehicle, the Cayenne. Today, SUVs make up a huge chunk of Porsche’s sales. The brand is now entering the race toward electrification – but this time the innovator is playing catch-up to others.

node.title: How Porsche went from sports cars to SUVs ... and EVs

node.text: It’s taken over two years, but these days Jeremy Mateo is finally feeling at home. Mateo, 27, is a real estate broker in Honolulu, Hawaii, and bought his first condo on Oahu island right before the coronavirus pandemic in March 2020. Over the course of a year he saved $60,000 for a down payment and worked toward his goal of buying his “dream home.” Then he spent another year renovating and furnishing his place. The last of his furniture arrived in spring 2021, finally closing the chapter on his homebuying journey. Here’s how Mateo bought his one-bedroom condo for $560,000. (With @CNBCMakeIt)

node.text: We have liftoff! Blue Origin’s New Shepard capsule launched into space Tuesday morning, carrying Jeff Bezos, Mark Bezos, Wally Funk and Oliver Daemen. 🚀✨

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on July 20, 2021. May be an image of ‎text that says '‎Morgan Stanley says a 10% to 20% correction is ahead I CNBC M اע‎'‎.

node.text:
New for subscribers: The stock market is teetering toward a correction, and investors should burrow down in some less volatile stocks, according to Morgan Stanley.⁠
⁠
The firm’s strategists, led by Michael Wilson, said Monday in a note that the market rally showed signs of being exhausted. “Market breadth has been deteriorating for months and is just another confirmation of the mid-cycle transition, in our view. It usually ends with a material (10-20%) index level correction,” the note said.⁠
⁠
What stocks does the firm say investors should turn to? Link in bio. (Try CNBC pro for 7 days for free!)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on July 19, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Blue Origin is launching Jeff Bezos to space on Tuesday. Here is what you should know CNBC'.

node.text:
Near a small town in the West Texas desert, a quartet led by the world’s richest person is preparing to launch on a historic flight to the edge of space. 🚀⁠
⁠
Blue Origin, the space company founded by Amazon executive chairman Jeff Bezos in 2000, has been testing prototypes of its New Shepard rocket and capsule for more than a decade. After 15 successful test flights without people on board, Blue Origin is set to put its spacecraft to the ultimate test: Its first human spaceflight. On Tuesday, the company plans to send Bezos and others to float in microgravity for a couple minutes, and return safely.⁠
⁠
Read more about what you should know about the crew, the rocket launching them and what the experience is expected to be like at the link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on July 19, 2021. May be an image of outdoors and text that says 'Viral video shows Malaysian police destroying 1,069 bitcoin mining rigs with a steamroller HAMI G CNBC'.

node.text:
Call it a crypto crackdown — literally.⁠
⁠
Malaysian authorities seized 1,069 bitcoin mining rigs, laid them out in a parking lot at police headquarters, and used a steamroller to crush them, as part of a joint operation between law enforcement in the city of Miri and electric utility Sarawak Energy.⁠
⁠
Assistant Commissioner of Police Hakemal Hawari told CNBC the crackdown came after miners allegedly stole $2 million worth of electricity siphoned from Sarawak Energy power lines. ⁠
⁠
Watch the viral video at the link in bio. 👀

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on July 19, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says '"We are are going to to have an extremely strong economy coming in the fall." Bill Ackman CNBC'.

node.text:
“You are going to see a massive, my view, economic boom."⁠
⁠
Billionaire investor Bill Ackman said Monday that the spread of the delta variant doesn’t pose a significant threat to the economic reopening, and he sees interest rates rising on the back of the big comeback.⁠
⁠
The hedge fund manager believes bond yields will trend much higher in the second half of 2021 as the economy continues to recover from the pandemic-induced recession. ⁠
⁠
Details on why Ackman says the slide in Treasury yields Monday provided investors with a buying opportunity at the link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on July 19, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Robinhood is seeking a market valuation as high as $35 billion in its upcoming IPO robinhood CNBC'.

node.text:
Robinhood is seeking a market valuation of as much as $35 billion in its upcoming initial public offering, according to an amended SEC filing released Monday. 💰⁠
⁠
The stock trading app will attempt to sell its share at a range of $38 to $42 per share, according to the updated prospectus. Robinhood is looking to sell 55 million shares at that range to raise as much as $2.3 billion. Robinhood’s last private market valuation was $11.7 billion as of September.⁠
⁠
Think you'll invest in the company when it goes public? Read the full article at the link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on July 18, 2021. May be an image of outdoors and text that says 'Investment in space companies hit record $4.5 billion in the second quarter, report says CNBC'.

node.text:
$4,500,000,000. 😮⁠
⁠
Private investment in space companies hit $4.5 billion in the second quarter, a record for the sector, according to a report by New York-based firm Space Capital.⁠
⁠
“This was the largest quarter on record for space infrastructure investment, despite only two space company SPACs closing in Q2,” Space Capital managing partner Chad Anderson wrote in the report.⁠
⁠
What drove the quarter's surge and what should you expect from the sector for the rest of the year? Link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on July 18, 2021. May be an image of sky, skyscraper and text that says 'These are the five Top States for Business in 2021 5. Tennessee W CNBC'.

node.text:
The pandemic changed the battle between the states for business and jobs, and the race to be America’s Top State for Business. ⁠⁠
⁠⁠
This year’s top 5 states in the annual CNBC study of state competitiveness reflect the strengths of some perennial favorites, but also recent rising states and a first-time top five finisher that excelled in categories that have grown in importance, and evolved.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
What were the strengths and weaknesses of each state to earn their top spots on the list? Link in bio.

Photo by CNBC on July 18, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'This 30-year-old quit his job to work on his side hustle. Now he's on track to make $200,000 in sales this year CNBC'.

node.text:
Sometimes it takes a major life event to push you in the right direction.⁠
⁠
Last April, @CNBCMakeIt contributor Jake Kenyon spent his birthday battling Covid-19 in his bedroom. His time quarantining forced him to think about his future and what really made him happy in life.⁠
⁠
While he liked his job, what he enjoyed even more was working on his side hustle, Kenyarn, selling hand-dyed yarn. With the pandemic driving more people to crafts like knitting and crocheting, sales on Shopify were skyrocketing. Gross sales jumped from $20,000 in 2019, when he started the side hustle, to $125,000 in 2020. In January, he quit his job to work on Kenyarn full-time.⁠
⁠
How did he turn his passion into a profitable full-time business? Link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on July 18, 2021. May be an image of body of water and text that says 'The Amazon rainforest is now releasing more carbon than it can absorb, study finds CNBC'.

node.text:
The Amazon rainforest is emitting more carbon emissions than it can absorb, according to a new study.⁠
⁠
The rainforest was once a carbon sink — meaning it absorbed more carbon than it released — but it now accounts for more than 1 billion metric tons of emissions every year, mainly due to forest fires and deforestation.⁠
⁠
How much carbon could the Amazon remove from the atmosphere without fires or deforestation? Link in bio for details.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on July 17, 2021. May be an image of ‎money and ‎text that says '‎China's share of global bitcoin mining plunges while Kazakhstan climbs to third place 一 IZED PEER TOPE ស PיW CNBC‎'‎‎.

node.text:
China’s share of global bitcoin mining plunged this year while Kazakhstan rose to become the world’s third-largest player in the industry, according to research from Cambridge University.⁠
⁠
The research shows China accounted for less than half (46%) of the power used for bitcoin mining in April, down sharply from 75.5% in September 2019. That’s before authorities ordered a crackdown on the mining of cryptocurrencies. Meanwhile, Kazakhstan saw an almost sixfold increase in its share of global bitcoin mining in the same period, climbing to 8.2% from 1.4%. ⁠
⁠
What share of bitcoin mining did the U.S. account for? Link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on July 17, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Facebook to pay creators $1 billion through 2022 CNBC'.

node.text:
Facebook CEO Mark Zuckerberg this week announced the company plans to pay out $1 billion through 2022 to users who create content for its Facebook and Instagram social networks.⁠
⁠
It’s one way the company hopes to attract influencers to create content for its platforms as it competes with other popular services like TikTok. As part of this initiative, the company plans to roll out new bonus programs between now and the end of the year that will pay out creators for hitting specific milestones, Facebook said in a statement.⁠
⁠
Details on those bonus programs and how you can potentially get paid at the link in bio. 👀
